    narr:narration """This hub defines the product identity, centering on the [curated expertise installation](narr:Position_ProductIsCuratedExpertiseInstallation) as the primary anchor. This framing, established in April 2026, serves as a corrective to previous pipeline errors; specifically, the system clarifies that [the product is NOT a phone number](narr:Position_ProductIsNotPhoneNumber), relegating SMS to a [context-dependent distribution channel](narr:Position_SMSIsDistributionChannel) rather than a core identity. The operational deliverable is defined as an [MCP server paired with three executive interviews](narr:Obs_ProductDeliverable). Beyond the commercial definition, the system's conceptual reach is anchored by the [personal graph founding insight](narr:Observation_CoreFraming) and the [lens tool definition](narr:Observation_ScarletLensDefinition), which emphasizes the necessity of identifying deltas between competing drafts. Stylistic observations note a deliberate [code-switching](narr:StyleObs_12) between analytical rigor and informal, unpunctuated conversational fragments, alongside the use of [metaphors like 'collective memory' and 'system sketch'](narr:StyleObs_SystemSketchMetaphor) to bridge the gap between technical output and human-centric utility.""" ;
